    {
      "id": "input-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2380,
      "y": 20,
      "width": 1020,
      "height": 500,
      "text": "Input doctrine\\n\\n- `raw/` holds books, papers, and clipped source material\\n- `catalog/` mirrors remote dataset descriptions and samples\\n- source notes compile chapter-by-chapter or section-by-section ingest\\n- the vault never treats giant remote parquet as local truth\\n- evidence returns as bounded artifacts, then gets crystallized back into markdown"
    },
